        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 1:59PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles southwest of Lincoln National Forest, moving
south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lincoln National Forest, Crow Flats, and Brokeoff Mountains.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
south central New Mexico.</instruction>
